st common reason.";i:5;s:91:"Or sometimes door wasnt installed properly and can rub against door opening when operating.";i:6;s:80:"Also if there is any damage to door or track will make a door difficult to open.";i:7;s:79:"The first thing on either type of door you may have is to inspect your springs.";i:8;s:50:"Safety Tips for Manually Opening Your Garage Door.";i:9;s:59:"When you open a garage door by hand make sure to stay safe.";i:10;s:33:"Unplug the automatic door opener.";i:11;s:115:"Unplugging the garage door opener before you try to manually open or reconnect your garage door will keep you safe.";i:12;s:120:"If the power comes back on the opener might attempt to open the door while it is disengaged which can make it harder to.";i:13;s:76:"If your garage door is not balanced right it wont go up or down all the way.";i:14;s:85:"To check the balance pull the emergency release cord or chain to disconnect the door.";i:15;s:60:"You should now be able to move the door up and down by hand.";i:16;s:41:"Why wont my garage door open all the way.";i:17;s:145:"Sometimes when it gets stopped halfway shut or open it might be that the springs are broken see 3 or the limit setting needs an adjustment see 7.";i:18;s:66:"If all else fails you might try spraying the track with lubricant.";i:19;s:384:"If you have an opener you will need to disengage it by pulling on the emergency release cord this will allow you to open the door freely by hand and you will want to put the garage door in the fully up position to work on the springs so you might need to have somebody help you by getting on the ladder if needed and holding that door in the up position so you can adjust the springs.";i:20;s:96:"To manually open most garage doors you simply pull a corded handle that is attached to the door.";i:21;s:88:"This disengages the electric drive from the door and you can manually open and close it.";i:22;s:64:"To reset it begin by pulling the cord in the opposite direction.";i:23;s:25:"It should click in place.";i:24;s:79:"It turns out that the manaul opening problem is related to the openers problem.";i:25;s:178:"My door installer came out yesterday he cant open it either so he took off the L-shape lever that connect the door to the drive chain from the motor and the door now open freely.";i:26;s:79:"I am waiting for the Genie guy to come to replace the opener together with the.";i:27;s:178:"If you click your remote and hear the garage door openers motor running but the door wont open the first thing you should do is check to see that the manual release isnt engaged.";i:28;s:129:"Usually located towards the front of your garage the manual release is that brightly-colored cord hanging down within easy reach.";i:29;s:92:"Enter the garage by the side door then you can open the main door using the internal handle.";i:30;s:100:"You can continue to use the door this way until you have the lock and or handle connection repaired.";i:31;s:112:"Both jobs are relatively simple and we would normally be able to do either as part of a standard call-out visit.";i:32;s:35:"If the external handle doesnt move.";i:33;s:64:"Garage door opener hand held wont work I have changed battreies.";i:34;s:69:"In it and onthe key pad on the door now the key pad wont work either.";i:35;s:48:"Only the button inside garage to open and close.";i:36;s:50:"What do I need to do before my husband comes home.";i:37;s:42:"Grab the door with both hands and lift it.";i:38;s:68:"If the door will not budge pull the cord harder until it locks open.";i:39;s:60:"If the door is too heavy for you to lift dont hurt yourself.";i:40;s:79:"If one of the wires is loose when you wiggle it it will cause the door to open.";i:41;s:45:"Shut off the power to the garage door opener.";i:42;s:38:"Use a screwdriver to tighten the wire.";i:43;s:93:"Garage door springs offset the weight of the garage door to open and close the door smoothly.";i:44;s:76:"These springs are featured in both manual and automatic garage d